<TITLE> Businessman testifies in Ramna blast case </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 5 (bdnews24.com) - A businessman, Nayeem Ullah, who suffered injuries in the bloody bombing at the Ramna Batamul during Bangla New Year celebrations testified Tuesday at Dhaka metropolitan sessions' judge's court. Judge ANM Bashir Ullah set May 21 and 22 for recording witnesses' statements. Ullah, testifying on behalf of the state, said the bombs went off at 8:05am and he started running for cover. He then realised that he was bleeding in the leg, his pants also soaked in blood, he said. Then he fainted.. Shrapnel also removed from his leg at Combined Military Hospital in Dhaka, he added. Police produced five accused, including Mufti Hannan, in the case, while the court was taking the businessman's statements. Maulana Akbar Hossain, who is now on bail, was also present at the court. Banned Islamist outfit Harkatul Jihad al-Islami, Bangladesh, chief Mufiti Hannan, who was being taken to jail after the court proceedings, shouted that the case was false and cursed state prosecutors and investigators. b
